The  regional  directors  of  the  World  Health  Organization  and  United  Nations  agencies  have  recorded  137  attacks  on  health  care  facilities  in  Gaza  since  the  fighting  began,  resulting  in  521  people  killed  and  686  injured.
According  to  the  groups,  16  health  care  workers  have  been  killed  and  38  have  been  injured  on  duty.

The  Palestinian  Health  Ministry  reports  more  than  11,000  people  in  Gaza  have  been  killed  in  Israeli  military  operations  since  the  Oct.  7  Hamas-led  attack  on  Israel  that  killed  about  1,200  people.
